# cybersecurity-task Steganography Tool for Image/File Hiding

#Command-used

steghide --help(
 is a steganography tool in Linux used to hide files inside image or audio files (like JPEG, BMP, WAV, AU) and to extract hidden data from such files. It uses encryption and compression for security.
)

steghide embed -cf stone.jpeg-ef sample-data.csv(
stone.jpeg: becomes a container with hidden data
sample-data.csv: The image still looks normal but now contains data
)

steghide extract -sf stone.jpeg(
Pulls out hidden file from image
Asks for password (if set)
Saves extracted file to current folder
)
